  "prompt": "I'm a shy guy and don't know how to talk to strangers. How do I make new friends at college?",
  "response": "Making new friends in college can feel daunting, but it's definitely manageable, especially when you put yourself out there in small ways. Here are some tips to help you connect with others:\n\n1. **Join Clubs and Organizations**: Look for clubs that interest you, whether they're related to your major, hobbies, or activities you enjoy. This gives you a natural conversation starter with people who share your interests.\n\n2. **Attend Campus Events**: Participate in social events, workshops, or lectures. These settings are often designed for meeting others, and you'll have the opportunity to strike up conversations.\n\n3. **Utilize Class Opportunities**: Engage with classmates before or after lectures. You can start with simple comments about the class or ask if they want to form a study group.\n\n4. **Be Approachable**: Smile and maintain open body language. Small gestures can make you seem more friendly and encourage others to approach you.\n\n5. **Use Social Media**: Join online groups or forums related to your college or interests. This can lead to meeting people in person later on.\n\n6. **Start Small**: Begin with casual conversations in common spaces like the dining hall, library, or study lounges. Simple questions or compliments can open the door to further dialogue.\n\n7. **Take the Initiative**: Don\u2019t be afraid to invite someone to join you for coffee or lunch. A simple, \u201cHey, would you like to grab a coffee sometime?\u201d can go a long way.\n\n8. **Volunteer**: Helping out with community service or campus initiatives can connect you with others while also making a positive impact.\n\n9. **Find a Buddy**: If you know someone in the same situation, approach it together. You can support each other in meeting new people.\n\n10. **Practice Active Listening**: When you do engage in conversations, show genuine interest in what the other person is saying. Ask follow-up questions and share your own experiences.\n\n11. **Be Patient**: Making friends takes time, so don\u2019t feel discouraged if it doesn\u2019t happen immediately. The more you put yourself out there, the easier it will become.\n\nRemember, many students are looking to make friends just like you are, so you're not alone in this!",
